                            <comment id="475627" author="adilger" created="Tue, 21 Oct 2025 14:59:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No, I&apos;m not sure that increasing the max delta is good. At some point the test just becomes meaningless. There is work being done under &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9&quot; title=&quot;Optimize weighted QOS Round-Robin allocator&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9&quot;&gt;LU-9&lt;/a&gt; that might help this test to be more consistent. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="475215" author="yujian" created="Thu, 16 Oct 2025 18:56:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The sanity/51d subtest passed consistently on the recent master builds in full group test sessions. It only failed sporadically on patch review test sessions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I saw the subtest was improved a couple of times before by the following patches:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/44762&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/44762&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12058&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_51d: @@@@@@ FAIL: OST 1 has less #0 objects vs OST 0 (0 &amp;lt; 1000&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12058&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12058&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: improve sanity test_51d reliability&quot;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/48086&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/48086&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14745&quot; title=&quot;sanity:  sanity test_51d: @@@@@@ FAIL: OST 2 has less objects vs OST 1  (134 &amp;lt; 161&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14745&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14745&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: ensure sanity/51d has enough objects&quot;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/46154&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/46154&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15282&quot; title=&quot;Don&amp;#39;t hold a spin locks during space alloc (rr policy)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15282&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-15282&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: improve sanity test_51d coverage&quot;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/47978&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/47978&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15282&quot; title=&quot;Don&amp;#39;t hold a spin locks during space alloc (rr policy)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15282&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-15282&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: relax test_51d thresholds somewhat&quot;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adilger&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;adilger&quot;&gt;adilger&lt;/a&gt;, could you please advise if we need to increase the &lt;b&gt;max&lt;/b&gt; value in &lt;tt&gt;test_51d_sub()&lt;/tt&gt; again to relax the threshold?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="472955" author="yujian" created="Thu, 25 Sep 2025 20:00:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;39 records found in the last 4 weeks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
